<p>
WIMS is used in the ``practice'' part of a mathematics course with weekly lectures given in amphitheaters and other practice sessions in conventional classrooms.
<p>
The course is a mixture of calculus, linear algebra and geometry. Subjects include linear systems, matrices, rank, vector spaces, bases, linear maps, real numbers, continuity, infinite sequences, Taylor expansion, primitives and integration, affine geometry, parametric curves.
